        <title>System Description</title>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>System Overview</title>
          <para>
            The Center Body system comprises multiple structural assemblies including 
            forward and aft bulkheads, center body skin panels, internal frames, and 
            stringers. These components work together to form the primary load-bearing 
            structure of the aircraft.
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>System Components</title>
          <para>
            Major components include: Forward Bulkhead Assembly, Aft Bulkhead Assembly, 
            Upper Skin Panels, Lower Skin Panels, Internal Frame Structure, Longitudinal 
            Stringers, and Interface Fittings for wing attachment.
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
